      "text": "> Output neurons compete to represent input\n> Similar to single-layer feed forward network except the\n  output neuron are connected to each other.\n> Used in unsupervised learning\n> Recurrent in nature(recurrent netowork)\n        -> Similar to multi-layer feed forward network except\n           the output can be fed back to the input or some layer.\n        -> Includes feedback connection\n        -> May contain self-loops.\n        -> Suitable for sequence and time-dependent data.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "> Output neurons compete to represent input\n> Similar to single-layer feed forward network except the\n  output neuron are connected to each other.\n> Used in unsupervised learning\n> Recurrent in nature(recurrent netowork)\n        -> Similar to multi-layer feed forward network except\n           the output can be fed back to the input or some layer.\n        -> Includes feedback connection\n        -> May contain self-loops.\n        -> Suitable for sequence and time-dependent data.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
